*** DOCUMENT BUILD HOW-TO ***

In order to build PDF documents locally, you must have a full Java Development 
Kit (JDK) installed on your local machine.  

You can download it here: http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html

=======================================

If you want to build a Jetstream 2.0 document, do the following:
----------------------------------------------------------------

1) Drop to a command-line prompt
2) Change directory to JS2.0
3) If on Windows - Run the build_document.bat file.
   If on Linux - Run the build_document.sh file.
4) Choose the top-level ditamap file of the document you want to build
5) The resulting PDF document will be output in the JS2.0/out/JS2.0 directory.